OL,3,CLabour's antisemitism problem is 'a
OL,4,Cmillion miles from where it was'
OL,6,F"It is a problem of society, and
OL,7,Fpolitics reflects society," he said.
OL,8,F"So, while there is a problem with
OL,9,Fantisemitism in the country as a
OL,10,Fwhole, it is always going to come into
OL,11,Fpolitics.
OL,13,F"It's about how we deal with it and
OL,14,Fhow we respond to it, and I appreciate
OL,15,Fwhat the Labour party is trying to do,
OL,16,Fit's unfortunate that once something
OL,17,Fhas been established - and there has
OL,18,Fbeen a problem in the Labour party -
OL,19,Fthen it's very easy for that to
OL,20,Fcontinue even if people are trying to
OL,21,Fdo things about it.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G8/13
